# Long-cache content-addressed bundles. Vite hashes every emitted
# entry, chunk, and asset under `_build/` — `assertHashedAssetNames`
# in `vite.config.ts` fails the build if a future config tweak ever
# drops `[hash]` from the output templates, so this prefix is safe
# to mark `immutable`.
#
# `Service-Worker-Allowed: /` widens the scope of the bundled
# service worker (which Vite emits under `/_build/` with a hashed
# name) past its default directory scope. The header is harmless on
# non-SW responses.
#
# Everything else inherits Cloudflare's default
# `Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate`, which keeps
# HTML shells (and anything else not under `_build/`) revalidating
# every request.

/_build/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Service-Worker-Allowed: /

# The PWA manifest MUST stay revalidating. Installed PWAs persist the
# manifest URL and re-fetch it directly (ignoring the `<link>` in fresh
# HTML), so a content-addressed/immutable manifest strands installs on
# a hash the next deploy deletes. It lives here at the root — off the
# `_build/` prefix — to inherit revalidation; this explicit rule pins
# that intent so a future change can't silently re-cache it. The hashed
# icons it references stay immutable under `_build/`.
/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
